Managing green microbusinesses. Understanding green consumers. Building a green brand. Sustainable quality management. Green product development and service design. Managing supply chains in green microbusinesses. Communication in a customer journey. Export and international markets.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the student's necessary business skills and make them think more thoroughly about the sustainable use of natural resources to meet the demands of consumers for environmentally friendly, natural, healthy products and services that offer maximum value to different parties.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) has an understanding of the need for sustainable management and sees green business opportunities; 2) describes the concept of a green consumer and ideas related to green branding; 3) knows the basics of quality management as well as the most common quality and/or environmental certifications; 4) is able to describe green products, processes, supply chain management and logistics; 5) knows design thinking and service design principles and different tools; 6) describes green communication opportunities in different stages of a customer journey; 7) understands the difference between local and international businesses, meaning of target markets and segmentation; 8) analyzes the compliance of processes with the principles of green entrepreneurship and makes suggestions for improvement.
